Assertions:
[NAV] Browser navigates to {picked_pdp_url}
[DOM] PDP page heading text contains {picked_pdp_name}
[STATE] Search dropdown closes after product click
[DOM] PDP renders product image, price, and primary action (qty stepper or Add-to-Cart) — no broken placeholders

Preconditions:
[PRE:CLEAR_SESSION]
- Browser viewport resized to 375px width (iPhone SE)
- Storefront accessible at {{FRONT_URL}}

Steps:
[NAV] Navigate to {{FRONT_URL}}
[SETUP] read test-data/search-queries/b2b-buyer-queries.csv, filter rows where query_type=brand-in-query, pick a random row → {picked_query}; extract the brand token (first word) → {brand_token}; extract the noun token (remaining words) → {noun_token}
[LOG] write {picked_query, brand_token, noun_token} to evidence
[ACT] Click the search input
[ACT] fill 'Search': {picked_query}
[KEY] press [Enter]
[WAIT] Wait for /search?q=… results page to load
[SETUP] browser_snapshot the results grid; capture the first product card's visible name → {first_card_name}; count how many of the top 5 cards' names contain {brand_token} (case-insensitive) → {brand_hit_count}
[LOG] append {first_card_name, brand_hit_count} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify at least 1 product card is rendered
[ASSERT] Verify {first_card_name} contains either {brand_token} OR {noun_token} (a brand-only or noun-only hit is acceptable; a card with neither indicates the search engine ignored both tokens)
[ASSERT] Verify {brand_hit_count} >= 1 in the top 5 (the brand token is ranked into the top results, not buried)

[NAV] Navigate to {{FRONT_URL}}
[SETUP] read test-data/search-queries/b2b-buyer-queries.csv, filter rows where query_type=color-in-query, pick a random row → {picked_query}; extract the color token (first word) → {color_token}; extract the noun token (remaining words) → {noun_token}
[LOG] write {picked_query, color_token, noun_token} to evidence
[ACT] Click the search input
[ACT] fill 'Search': {picked_query}
[KEY] press [Enter]
[WAIT] Wait for /search?q=… results page to load
[SETUP] browser_snapshot the results grid; capture the first card's name → {first_card_name}; if a Color facet is present in the sidebar, capture whether {color_token} appears as a facet value → {color_in_facet}
[LOG] append {first_card_name, color_in_facet} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify at least 1 product card is rendered (NOT zero — color+noun should not return empty)
[ASSERT] Verify {first_card_name} contains {noun_token} (the product-type semantics carried through)
[ASSERT] Verify either: {first_card_name} contains {color_token} (color is in the product name) OR the Color facet shows {color_token} as a value (color matched via attribute) — pick whichever the storefront supports
